 buyTokens directly when purchasing tokens from a contract.

params.value: value of wei or token paid for purchase

buyTokens(address,uint256).details: low level token purchase with a token ***DO NOT OVERRIDE*** This function has a non-reentrancy guard, so it shouldn't be called by another `nonReentrant` function.

params._tokenAmount: Value in wei or token involved in the purchase

buyTokensEth(address).details: low level token purchase with ETH ***DO NOT OVERRIDE*** This function has a non-reentrancy guard, so it shouldn't be called by another `nonReentrant` function.

finalize().details: Must be called after crowdsale ends, to do some extra finalization work. Calls the contracts finalization function.

goal().notice: minimum amount of funds to be raised in weis or tokens

goalReached().details: Checks whether funding goal was reached.

hasClosed().details: Checks whether the period in which the crowdsale is open has already elapsed.

params._funder: The address that funds the token for crowdsale
params._goal: Minimum amount of funds to be raised in weis or tokens
params._paymentCurrency: The currency the crowdsale accepts for payment. Can be ETH or token address
params._rate: Number of token units a buyer gets per wei or token
params._token: Address of the token being sold
params._totalTokens: The total number of tokens to sell in crowdsale
params._wallet: Address where collected funds will be forwarded to

returns._0: true if the crowdsale is open, false otherwise.

marketTemplate().notice: MISOMarket template id for the factory contract

paymentCurrency().notice: The currency the crowdsale accepts for payment. Can be ETH or token address

rate().notice: How many token units a buyer gets per token or wei. The rate is the conversion between wei and the smallest and indivisible token unit. So, if you are using a rate of 1 with a ERC20Detailed token with 3 decimals called TOK 1 wei will give you 1 unit, or 0.001 TOK.
